      <p id="Par40">The package implements a number of distinct scores for model-selection, but the model in Fig.Â <xref rid="Fig2" ref-type="fig">2</xref>a is selected by using reICL. In this case all the scores available in the package rank the output model first, meaning that they consistently predict the model in Fig.Â <xref rid="Fig2" ref-type="fig">2</xref>a to be the best possible fit for the input data (Fig.Â <xref rid="Fig2" ref-type="fig">2</xref>d). The tool also offers visualization functions that can at least suggest, even from a single model fit, what is the stability of the clustering. This information is linked to modelâs latent variablesâdenoted with <inline-formula id="IEq60"><alternatives><tex-math id="M137">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
